Content:
It&#x27;s probably not a good idea to start using blockchains for everything. (As much as I dig bitcoin and all.) Shudder.<p>What about a simple proposal for the convention of firing a query for a mailing address before each mailing, by such means as:<p><pre><code>    1. HTTP request to (something like) &quot;/address.txt&quot;
    2. *blank* email with subject line (such as) &quot;address&quot;
</code></pre>
I wonder how difficult it would be to get the whole world on board with this, to the extent that a domain name or email address is accepted in form fields requiring mailing addresses.
